### Why 1-node works but 2-node fails

Intra-node GPU communication uses **XGMI** (direct GPU-to-GPU links on
MI250X) which doesn't need the OFI plugin. The plugin is only needed for
**inter-node** collectives over Slingshot.

### Single-node: NCCL_NET must NOT be set

The aws-ofi-rccl plugin (commit `339b39d`) fails to initialize on
single-node jobs because the CXI fabric is not active for intra-node
communication. Setting `NCCL_NET="AWS Libfabric"` makes NCCL treat
this as a fatal error ("Failed to initialize any NET plugin") instead
of falling back to XGMI.

`config/frontier.yaml` lists `NCCL_NET` and `NCCL_NET_PLUGIN` under
`multinode-only-env` so they are automatically omitted for single-node
jobs. The other Slingshot-related env vars (FI_CXI_*, HSA_*, etc.) are
harmless on single-node and are kept.

### Verified NCCL output (working)

When the plugin loads correctly, NCCL_DEBUG=INFO shows:
```
NET/AWS Libfabric/0/GDRDMA          # OFI plugin active with GDR
GPU Direct RDMA Enabled for GPU 0   # RDMA from GPU memory
ncclCommInitRankConfig_impl ... Init COMPLETE
```

### Other fixes applied

- **Overlay on /tmp**: `fuse-overlayfs` doesn't work on Lustre; moved
  Apptainer overlay to `/tmp/omnihub-overlay.$SLURM_PROCID` (node-local NVMe).
- **HTTP proxy**: Compute nodes need `http_proxy=http://proxy.ccs.ornl.gov:3128`
  for PyPI access (added to `config/frontier.yaml` prelude-commands).
- **Workspace override**: `pretrain_wrapper.py` now redirects Primus
  `workspace` to `$OMNIHUB_RESULTS_DIR` to avoid writing inside read-only container.
- **hf_assets_path**: Set explicitly in config to avoid HF_TOKEN requirement
  even with `mock_data: true` (tokenizer still needs model assets).
- **Sanity check**: Skip NCCL sanity check for multi-node debug runs — it
  runs plain `apptainer exec` without bind mounts, so the OFI plugin always
  fails and the test hangs on TCP sockets.
- **MIOpen cache**: Set `MIOPEN_USER_DB_PATH=/tmp/$SLURM_JOB_ID` to avoid
  Lustre I/O issues with MIOpen kernel cache.
